aked-mole-rat-queens-emit-a-special-scent-to-stop-their-rivals-from-reproducing-a-new-study-suggests-180989148/</guid></item><item><title>附近的世界上可能存在生命吗？天文学家首次在宜居带的类地系外行星上发现了大气层</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-life-exist-on-this-nearby-world-in-a-first-astronomers-find-an-atmosphere-on-an-earth-like-exoplanet-in-the-habitable-zone-180989149/</link><description>虽然这个天体似乎拥有三个可以创造宜居环境的特征——大气层、岩石成分和可以让液态水停留在表面的温度——但研究人员目前尚未发现任何居民</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 16:23:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-life-exist-on-this-nearby-world-in-a-first-astronomers-find-an-atmosphere-on-an-earth-like-exoplanet-in-the-habitable-zone-180989149/</guid></item><item><title>一位业余天文学家使用谷歌地图发现了一个奇怪的凹痕。原来是3.9亿年前的陨石坑</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-amateur-astronomer-using-google-maps-spotted-a-strange-indentation-it-turned-out-to-be-a-meteorite-crater-from-390-million-years-ago-180989158/</link><description>科学家们通过对魁北克遗址的考察证实了天文学家的怀疑。这一发现提供了一个罕见的案例，即报道的新陨石坑被证明是真实的</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 12:58:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-amateur-astronomer-using-google-maps-spotted-a-strange-indentation-it-turned-out-to-be-a-meteorite-crater-from-390-million-years-ago-180989158/</guid></item><item><title>伦敦塔计划将其护城河变成“绿色教室”，并在一次重大翻修中展示其建筑档案</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-tower-of-london-plans-to-turn-its-moat-into-a-green-classroom-and-show-off-its-architecture-archive-in-a-major-renovation-180989161/</link><description>这座具有近千年历史的地标建筑曾是国王的住所、皇家处决场所并守护着英国的皇冠上的宝石。新的教育中心旨在邀请更多人了解这段历史</description><pubDate>Mon, 20 Jul 2026 21:36:53 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-tower-of-london-plans-to-turn-its-moat-into-a-green-classroom-and-show-off-its-architecture-archive-in-a-major-renovation-180989161/</guid></item><item><title>一只外号为吉莫西、长相奇特的浣熊因其短而圆的身体在互联网上赢得